post_cb({"22647552": {"ParentId": "22647524", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>That <code>TabuSearch(vector&lt;Nodo&gt; n):nod(n);</code> shouldn't have compiled.  You're only allowed to put a ctor-initializer list on the construction definition, not merely a forward declaration.</p>\n<p>You almost certainly wanted:</p>\n<pre><code>TabuSearch(vector&lt;Nodo&gt; n):nod(n) {}\n</code></pre>\n<p>which has a body (albeit empty), and therefore is a definition.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>NOTE: Since you say that <code>clang</code> allowed compilation to finish and proceed to linking, that bug should be reported to the clang team.  12.6.2p1 is pretty clear that ctor-initializer requires a definition, not a non-defining declaration:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_22647524_22647552_0\">In the definition of a constructor for a class, initializers for direct and virtual base subobjects and non-static data members can be speci\ufb01ed by a ctor-initializer ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n</hr>", "OwnerUserId": "103167", "LastEditorUserId": "103167", "LastEditDate": "2014-03-25T22:42:55.267", "Id": "22647552", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2014-03-25T22:22:08.490", "LastActivityDate": "2014-03-25T22:42:55.267"}, "22647524": {"CommentCount": "6", "AcceptedAnswerId": "22647552", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "103167", "CreationDate": "2014-03-25T22:20:37.800", "LastActivityDate": "2014-03-25T22:42:55.267", "LastEditDate": "2014-03-25T22:30:02.483", "ViewCount": "57", "FavoriteCount": "2", "Title": "how can i give a vector of struct as parameter in the constructor of a class c++?", "Id": "22647524", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>my struct:</p>\n<pre><code>struct Nodo {\nfloat x;\nfloat y;\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>my class:</p>\n<pre><code>class TabuSearch{\n    vector&lt;Nodo&gt; nod;\npublic:\n    TabuSearch(vector&lt;Nodo&gt; n):nod(n);\n\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>my main</p>\n<pre><code>int num_ciudades = 30;\nvector&lt;Nodo&gt; nodo(num_ciudades);\nTabuSearch t(nodo);\n</code></pre>\n<p>I am getting this error on xcode:</p>\n<p>Undefined symbols for architecture x86_64:\n  \"<code>TabuSearch::TabuSearch(std::__1::vector&lt;Nodo, std::__1::allocator&lt;Nodo&gt; &gt;)</code>\", referenced from:\n      <code>_main</code> in main.o\nld: symbol(s) not found for architecture x86_64\nclang: error: linker command failed with exit code 1 (use -v to see invocation)</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c><xcode><class><struct>", "OwnerUserId": "3280686", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_22647524_22647552_0": {"section_id": 428, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n3337": {"so_22647524_22647552_0": {"section_id": 420, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n4659": {"so_22647524_22647552_0": {"section_id": 446, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}}});